description: Aspose.Imaging for .NET is an imaging library that lets developers create, edit, draw or convert images in their .NET applications. Aspose.Imaging provides features that go beyond the native capabilities of the development platform. It works independent of other applications and although Aspose.Imaging allows you to save to Adobe PhotoShop® format (PSD), you do not need PhotoShop on the machine.
releaseNotes:
Aspose.Imaging for .Net has been updated to version 3.8.0 and we are pleased to announce it
      Aspose.Imaging for .Net has been updated to version 3.8.0 and we are pleased to announce it.
      The following is a list of changes in this version of Aspose.Imaging.
      
      New features:
      IMAGINGNET-1567 Support Wmf file format
      IMAGINGNET-1863 Support for Diacom DCM image format
      IMAGINGNET-1855 Conversion of SVG to PNG
      IMAGINGNET-1832 Conversion of SVG to JPG
      IMAGINGNET-1828 Support for WMF for possible conversion to raster images
      IMAGINGNET-1827 Support for SVG to Raster Image Conversion	
      
      Enhancements:
      IMAGINGNET-1984 Unable to read file. Exception: The method or operation is not implemented: Exception while loading a TIFF file
      IMAGINGNET-1983 Exception while loading a PNG image: Could not read data
      IMAGINGNET-1633 Support to get the last modified day information on images
      IMAGINGNET-1630 Exporting images in multi threaded environment is not working
      IMAGINGNET-1629 Unable to load a JPG image - Image loading failed exception
      
      Exceptions
      IMAGINGNET-1614 Jpeg2000 to Jpeg export fault

summary: Aspose.Imaging for .NET is an imaging library that lets developers create, edit, draw or convert images in their .NET applications. Aspose.Imaging provides features that go beyond the native capabilities of the development platform. It works independent of other applications and although Aspose.Imaging allows you to save to Adobe PhotoShop® format (PSD), you do not need PhotoShop on the machine.
